<TITLE> Dhk-Ctg rail link snapped </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 23 (bdnews24.com)  Train communication between Dhaka and Chittagong remained halted from Sunday morning after a freight train went off the track in Comilla. The Dhaka bound train coming from Chittagong derailed at around 9:30am between Rasulpur and Razapur railway stations, five kilometres from Comilla town, a railway officer said. A rescue operation to remove the derailed train has already started. Rail connection will resume by 1:30pm, said Ibrahim Khalil, station manger of the railway's eastern zone. He told bdnews24.com that the Dhaka bound Subarna Express, stranded in Comilla due to the derailment, might reach Dhaka about two hours later than its scheduled time. bdne
